headline: Estée Lauder Expands Bumble And Bumble Reach With SalonCentric Partnership
summary: Bumble and bumble, part of Estée Lauder Companies, has entered a partnership with SalonCentric to distribute its products and education offerings across more than 850 stores in the U.S. The agreement extends to SalonCentric's digital platforms, broadening access for salons and stylists nationwide. The move aims to deepen engagement with beauty professionals and expand Bumble and bumble's presence in the U.S. professional haircare market. For investors watching Estée Lauder Companies...

headline: Is Estée Lauder (EL) Fairly Priced After Strong 1-Year Rebound And Long-Term Slump
summary: If you are wondering whether Estée Lauder Companies shares still offer value at around US$115, this article will help you size up the price tag before you commit fresh capital. The stock has had a mixed run, with a 2% decline over the last week, a 10.1% gain over the past month, 8% year to date, a 40.6% return over the last year, but declines of 54.8% over three years and 54.6% over five years. These swings have kept Estée Lauder on many investors' watchlists, as the share price has moved...
